Some say open source is an ideology, but I think it&#39;s a better way to code.
The community helps and does what one cannot invent or be able to do by oneself.
The 55-year-old Widenius is one of the most well-known promoters of open source code, along with another Finn, Linux developer Linus Torvalds.
Widenius helps other companies develop functional business models on top of open source code.
I still give 4-5 speeches every year in different parts of the world on this topic.
