A few months earlier, readers would have known they would get reliable information about the abduction from Valdez&#39;s column.
&quot;In the past, we would have already known what had happened,&quot; says 46-year-old Villarreal, who has received the nickname &quot;El Flaco&quot;, Ohukainen, due to his slender body structure.
&quot;Now all connections to our data sources are broken.&quot;
Valdez&#39;s office has been turned into a warehouse where signs and stickers against the persecution of journalists are stored. The newspaper&#39;s employees have received a new, unexpected task: they have become activists pushing for press freedom.
